!! Chapter Overview
The chapter starts out with John the Baptist around the Jordan "proclaiming a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins" (v3). John the Baptist talks about someone else who was to come who was greater than him (v16).

Eventually Jesus is baptized (v21-22) and we see that "the heavens were opened, and the Holy Spirit descended on him in bodily form, like a dove; and a voice came from heaven, "You are my beloved Son; with you I am well pleased." We see this voice affirming who Jesus was, the Son of God.

The second half of the chapter, we a genealogy of Jesus tracing back to Adam, the first human being. Some people who were in the list include:

* Abraham (Genesis 12) 
** Promise: Genesis 15
* Isaac (Genesis 21) 
** Promise: Genesis 26:1-5
* Jacob (Genesis 25) 
** Promise: Genesis 35:1-15 
* David (1 Samuel 16)
** Promise: 2 Samuel 7:12-13

People who we know are in the Old Testament and God had made certain promises through their descendants. There are also others not listed but I encourage people to go through. One of the promises being that there will be a great man who will establish God's kingdom forever (2 Samuel 7:12-13).

